The lessons feel rushed, and the explanations are often unclear‚Äîespecially when trying to follow along with coding. The instructor also has a heavy accent, which makes it even harder to keep up when everything is moving so quickly.

Overall, this course left me more frustrated and confused than confident. If you‚Äôre a true beginner hoping to understand data science step-by-step, this might not be the right fit. I really hope the instructor slows down and explains things more thoroughly in future updates.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
I'm really disappointed with this course. The explanations feel rushed, unclear, and lack proper depth. Important concepts are either skipped or explained so poorly that it becomes frustrating to keep up, even after just a few modules.

Many topics are simply skimmed over, as if the learner already knows them‚Äîwhich makes no sense, especially since this course is meant for beginners. It leaves you confused and constantly needing to look things up elsewhere.

It also seems like Krish Naik has just compiled videos from his YouTube channel and possibly reused content from other platforms where he‚Äôs taught before. For a paid course, this kind of recycled and disorganized content is just not acceptable and very unprofessional.

What‚Äôs worse is that many free YouTube videos from other instructors actually show much more effort and sincerity in breaking down complex topics. This course, on the other hand, feels like a half-hearted attempt that doesn‚Äôt live up to expectations. Honestly, I ended up learning most of the important concepts through textbooks and other online resources rather than from this course.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
I recently completed Krish Naik‚Äôs Data Science course on Udemy, and I must say it exceeded all my expectations. As someone who comes from a non-technical background, I was initially overwhelmed by the complexity of Data Science, but Krish's teaching style made everything so much easier to understand.

Krish Naik is not just an instructor he's a mentor. He breaks down complex concepts into simple, practical steps and always backs theory with hands-on coding and real-world use cases. What I appreciated the most was how he focused on both foundations (Python, statistics, ML algorithms) and industry projects, giving me confidence to apply what I learned in real scenarios.

The course content is very well-structured and up-to-date with the latest trends in the industry. Whether it‚Äôs data preprocessing, model training, or deploying ML models every topic is explained with clarity and depth.

If you're serious about building a career in Data Science, I highly recommend this course. Thank you, Krish Naik, for sharing your expertise and making Data Science approachable and exciting!

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
Honest Course Review ‚Äì What Worked Well & What Could Be Better

What I Liked:
1. The sections on Python and Supervised Machine Learning were well-structured and easy to follow.
2. ANN (Artificial Neural Networks) in the Deep Learning section was explained clearly and made the concept approachable.
3. The math explanations were done just right ‚Äî focusing on what‚Äôs essential without going deep into lengthy derivations. That really helped keep the pace up.
4. NLP was also covered quite well, with decent clarity on foundational concepts.

What Could Be Improved:
1. The word ‚Äúprobably‚Äù was used a lot throughout the explanations. Since the subjects already involve probability and statistics, this made some parts feel a bit uncertain or repetitive. Using it more selectively would make the delivery stronger and more confident.
2. The Unsupervised Learning topics didn‚Äôt get the same level of attention or clarity as the Supervised ones. The explanation style here felt less confident and a bit rushed.
3. In the Deep Learning section, advanced topics like CNN, RNN, LSTM, GRU were not explained very well. I found them a bit confusing, and honestly, external blogs provided better clarity. The examples used didn‚Äôt always connect well, but with the strong basics from earlier sections, these topics can still be self-learned afterward.
4. There were no quizzes, assignments, or case studies to practice the ML, DL concepts. 

Final Thoughts:
I took this course as a crash course to quickly refresh and reinforce core AI/ML concepts without spending too much time searching all over the internet. For a beginner-level course at this price, it gives a solid bird‚Äôs-eye view of the field and builds a good foundation.

It took 4 months for me to finish this completely ‚Äî though since I‚Äôm not a complete beginner, I could move faster. For someone entirely new to these topics, it might take a bit longer to get through everything comfortably.

Beginner Tip: Don't focus/stress too much on the Deployment part in the beginning, first get comfortable with EDA, Feature Engineering, Modelling, HyperParameter Tuning, Evaluation. Once you get comfortable with this then jump to MLOps as a separate topic for deployment.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
This course has been one of the most complete and enriching learning experiences I‚Äôve taken in the field of data science. It combines deep theoretical foundations ‚Äî including the mathematical intuition behind many algorithms ‚Äî with hands-on code-along sessions that push you to apply what you‚Äôre learning.

What I appreciated most was the way Krish explains theory: he uses a digital notebook-style blackboard, writing and walking through each concept step by step ‚Äî almost like attending a university lecture. This approach is used specifically during theoretical explanations, and helps make complex ideas more digestible before transitioning to hands-on coding separately.

What sets this course apart is how it doesn‚Äôt stop at model training. It extends into deployment and MLOps, which are often overlooked but critical skills for building real-world ML systems.

Some sections may feel dense if you‚Äôre not already familiar with the core ideas, but I see that as part of the challenge and growth. It‚Äôs a course that respects the learner and expects you to engage deeply.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
I really liked the way he taught everything, he even repeated some topics so that after listening to it again and again we get the points that we might i missed earlier.
But one thing is that there were some gaps in it, I understand that everything cannot be taught in great depth but still I would have loved a greater depth in this with all the mathematics needed, like exactly how backpropagation works for LSTM, transformers etc.
The practical implementations are also really good with deployment and all, just keep the content a bit updated as AWS has changed a bit, but the ML and DL part was really great.
Over all this course is worth it and if you not looking for mathematical intuitions, to become a researcher, this is a really good course to start with.

Also if you're looking to just learn the coding part, just skim over the in depth intuition, or skip it for later, and focus on coding part.
Now I am discovering unsupervised algorithms and it's getting interesting!
Hope you enjoy your learning too, make it your passion! You'd love it this way.

content:
This course doesn‚Äôt seem suitable for beginners, and I find it disappointing, Krish sir. The primary issue is the speed at which you are teaching. It would be helpful if you could slow down, especially when explaining the basics, as students need time to grasp foundational concepts. 

I feel this approach is not considerate of students who are just starting out. While the content might be great, the delivery doesn't work for me. I wish to request a refund, as the pace and teaching style are not aligned with my preferred way of learning. I believe it‚Äôs important to acknowledge that every student learns differently. PAISA BARBADH :(

I especially enjoyed the funny moments during the practical sessions, like whenever Krish Sir writes the word 'add'  üòÇ, of course that was just mis-typing.

Jokes aside,
What stood out the most is how effortlessly Krish Sir breaks down complex topics into a very simpler way. It‚Äôs an amazing course packed with clear and thorough explanations. From my side this course is highly recommended.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content: While I would like to give a 5 star rating for covering all the important topics, this course lacks the patience to explain the details that are required for a beginner in the field. If you have the mental energy to read between the lines and fill the gaps in the course, you can still complete. Else, this course is a bit difficult. It also looks like some videos posted here in the course are brought from another course elsewhere as the instructor keeps mentioning that there was a certain concept discussed earlier which was never discussed in the first place. Instructor misrepresents and misuses mathematical notations such as using eta for epsilon and epsilon for eta. I mean such mistakes are a no brainer and someone who has an attention to detail would not find it pleasing (which is a basic skill for a data scientist). I would second with the courses posted by Jose Portilla who explains concepts in a much better way and easy to follow along. Overall it is such a shame that this course despite of the great potential it had, is one among the falling stars.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
This course is truly an eye-opener for anyone wanting to dive into the world of Data Science, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and Natural Language Processing. It covers everything from the basics to advanced concepts, offering both depth and clarity in a way that's easy to follow. The real value lies in the way complex topics are explained simply, making them accessible to learners at all levels.

The hands-on exercises and practical examples are what really set this course apart. Instead of just theory, you actually get to work with the concepts, which makes everything stick. The opportunity to apply what you're learning in real-time is invaluable and helps reinforce the lessons in a way that just reading about them can‚Äôt.

What makes this course even better is Krish‚Äôs teaching style. He's got a way of breaking down tough topics into bite-sized, understandable pieces, all while keeping things fun and interactive. He genuinely engages with everyone, making sure no one falls behind and everyone stays motivated throughout the course.

If you‚Äôre looking to get into Data Science, ML, DL, or NLP, or just want to level up your skills, this course is absolutely worth your time. Whether you‚Äôre a beginner or someone with some experience, you'll walk away with a deeper understanding and practical skills that you can immediately apply.

content: I‚Äôve been following Krish Naik for over three years, but this course was honestly disappointing. The explanations feel rushed and lack depth. While it‚Äôs impressive to see over 100 hours of video material, the overall structure and delivery really need improvement. The topics are rushed, the concepts are not explained clearly, and the course doesn‚Äôt offer anything fresh or well-organized.  If you‚Äôre thinking about buying it, I‚Äôd honestly recommend checking out his YouTube channel first everything in this course is already there for free. Save your money.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
As a data science practitioner, I find the course content to be well-structured. However, the quality of the material provided is lacking. The explanations are often inconsistent and lack clarity, particularly for many algorithms. In several instances, I've found the explanations to be incorrect. For example, the explanation of the Gradient Boosting Regressor is below standard and contains inaccuracies. By comparing it with the content on the StatQuest YouTube channel, the difference becomes evident. This is just one of the instances I am highlighting but there are other inaccuracies as well.

A note to learners: Do not rely solely on these lectures. It is advisable to consult additional resources to solidify your understanding of the concepts.

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
1) Chapter 3: Instructions to download and install Anaconda, then navigating through command prompt vs IDE are too fast and seem to assume that the learner already is hands-on with what is being taught / shown.

2) Chapter 4: Similar to feedback for Chapter 3. Also, when the module on Github is provided later, it is not fair to expect the learner to be familiar with the Github IDE or even with command prompt while in this module.
I also noticed the instructor mentioning 'Open Code' instead of 'Open VS Code'. Please be correct.

3) Please avoid using the word 'probably' as you would do in a casual video. Please provide accurate instructions as this is an instructional training and not a nice-to-know supplementary guide.

4) Chapter 4: Too much technical content and jargons at the start of the course. Please break down content of Chapter 3, 4 and teach the basics first as separate earlier chapters for fresh learners.

5) Avoid too much Alt+Tab-bing while teaching on video. This is confusing.

Sorry, really DISAPPOINTED given all the excitement I had!!

course_name: Complete Data Science, Machine Learning, DL, NLP Bootcamp
content:
As someone with experience in data science, I can see that Krish is extremely knowledgeable. I truly appreciate your effort, attitude, and enthusiasm towards teaching. I‚Äôve followed some of your YouTube content and really value your goodwill in sharing your knowledge. However, I feel that this course could benefit from more structure to better align with the depth of your expertise.

While you clearly understand the material, the delivery often feels unorganized. It seems like the lessons were recorded without a clear script, leading to a lack of focus on which points need to be addressed and in what sequence. As a result, explanations sometimes become vague, and key concepts can get lost amidst repetition. This makes the videos lengthy, and despite the time invested, the core ideas don‚Äôt always come through as clearly as they should.

Along with all of your courses, I purchased and went through all other bestselling courses on Machine Learning and Deep Learning. Unfortunately, I felt that this course falls short in terms of preparation, clarity, and explanation compared to others.

More concise explanations and better preparation before each session would significantly improve the learning experience, helping students grasp the material more easily.

I genuinely admire your passion for teaching, and I believe that with some refinement, this course has the potential to be much stronger. Wishing you continued success, and I hope this feedback helps improve future iterations of the course.
